Etmopterus sheikoi
from Taiwanese waters ( Squaliformes : Etmopteridae )

The lanternshark genus 

Etmopterus

is one of the most diverse groups among all extant shark genera, comprising 41 valid species (

). They are widely distributed from tropical to subpolar oceans, at a depth range of 
50–4,500 m
(

). They are mostly small sharks, including the smallest known shark species, i.e., the dwarf lanternshark 

E. perryi
Springer & Burgess, 1985

(
